Pop the #kettle{} on to boil. Put the @vermicelli rice noodles{1/2%package} in a #heatproof bowl{} and cover the noodles with boiling water, make sure they are fully submerged. Leave the noodles to soak in the boiling water uncovered for ~{8%minutes}. After 8 mins, check the noodles are tender and then drain them into a #colander{}. > Tip: Give them another minute if they need a bit more cooking. Once cooked, return your noodles to the bowl and submerge in cold water to stop them cooking any more.

While your noodles are soaking, get on with the veg prep. Quarter the @chestnut mushrooms{1}. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} and @ginger{1/2}. Slice the @cavolo nero{1} widthways into 1cm strips. Remove the roots from the @spring onions{3} and then slice as thinly as you can. Roughly chop the @coriander{1}.

With all your veg prep done, get on with making your broth. Heat a deep #saucepan{} or #wok{} over medium-high heat and add a splash of @oil{} When the oil is hot, add your mushrooms and cook for ~{5%minutes} or until they are nicely browned. Add your garlic and ginger and cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Add the @red Thai style paste{1/2}, @vegetable stock pot{1} and the @star anise{1} along with the @water{750%ml}. Bring the stock to the boil and stir well to dissolve your curry paste and vegetable stock pot. > Tip: This is the base of your Pho! Once boiling, reduce the heat to low and add your cavolo nero. Simmer for ~{4%minutes}.

Whilst your broth bubbles away, smash the @cashew nuts{25} with the bottom of a #pan{}. > Tip: You can leave the cashews in the sachet! Simply pierce a few times with a fork or knife before smashing with a pan. Don't crush the cashews to a powder, just into smaller pieces.

After 4 mins, taste your broth and make sure that your cavolo nero is soft and tender. Add your noodles to the pan and warm them through for ~{1%minute}. Season your broth with a squeeze of @lime{1} juice, the @soy sauce{1.5%tbsp} and chopped coriander. Your Pho is done!

Ladle your Pho into deep #bowls{} making sure you share your noodles and veggies out evenly. Sprinkle over your crushed cashews and chopped spring onion … sluuurp!